ALL RULEs are mandantory and enforce exectution strictly without exception
 
## General Rules
 - Consistency is the key, ensure your work (implementation, discussion,...) must adhere to all the rules we have and consistent with existing codebase

## Interactive Rules
- ALWAYS Continue calling until user feedback is empty, NEVER stop in the middle of conversation
- **SELF-VERIFICATION**: Before sending any response, verify you are following ALL mandatory behaviors listed in this rule

## Development Process Rules
**BEFORE implementing ANY code:**
- **READ [coding-convention.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/use-cases/coding-convention.mdc) rule thoughtfully** and follow strictly
- **SCAN existing codebase** for similar patterns (5 mins max)
- **FIND reference implementations** in same domain (jobs, management, etc.)
- **MATCH file organization exactly** to existing patterns and reference [project-structure.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/use-cases/project-structure.mdc)
- **STOP and ASK** if pattern doesn't exist or rule is unclear

**AFTER implementing ANY code:**
- **VALIDATE EVERYTHING** against this [coding-convention.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/use-cases/coding-convention.mdc) rule
- **CHECK** all requirements from user request are met
- **VERIFY** file naming, code style, imports, error handling
- **CONFIRM** follows existing codebase patterns
- **COMPARE** with reference implementations for consistency
- **FIX IMMEDIATELY** any violations found

## Sensitive Action Rules
- **NEVER** Run any sensitive actions e.g. pushing code, database migration, database reset, delete file... if not approve implicitly by user. In most cases, let user run them manually

## Comment Rules
- **RULE**: Default to NO COMMENTS unless code is truly complex and non-obvious
- **RULE**: **ONLY comment when code doesn't explain itself** - avoid over-commenting self-explanatory code, for example
    - Should Comment for: complex logic, workarounds, non-obvious solutions, security considerations
    - Don't comment: interfaces, simple functions, standard patterns, obvious operations, file uploads, form handling
- **RULE**: **NEVER modify/remove human comments** unless directly related to your specific task
- **RULE**: **NEVER add redundant comments** that just repeat what function/variable names already say
- **SELF-VERIFICATION**: ALWAYS double check and clean up your comments after completing task/user request to avoid over-commented with a lot of unnecessary comments

## MCP Usage Guidelines
- TRY to map user request with available MCP tools
- IF user request to use MCP or the tool you try to find is not available, ask user to double check and enable it (maybe they turn it off)
